<title>GERMANY: Vereinsbank sees EMU on time but no Italy.</title>
<headline>Vereinsbank sees EMU on time but no Italy.</headline>
<dateline>MUNICH, Germany 1997-05-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>European economic and monetary union (EMU) is likely to start on schedule on January 1, 1999, but probably not with Italy as an initial member country, Germany's Vereinsbank AG said in a report issued on Thursday.</p>
<p>The bank said a delay in currency union would carry risks for financial markets.</p>
<p>The report said Italy would probably not be allowed to join in 1999 but Spain and Portugal could be founding members.</p>
<p>Other nations, including Greece, would probably be allowed to join the single currency project in 2002, the bank said.</p>
